On their own, these do not fill out the whole mitogenome, but when combined with scaffolds from the previous round, they manage to cover the whole mitogenome and can be merged with no gaps. Note that contig `Contig02+2968` is incorrectly assembled, when the assembler got to the long stretch of C's in the first repeat, it started assembling reads from the long stretch of C's in the second repeat, producing a chimera - not difficult to disentangle given information from our other samples, and luckily both repeats managed to be assembled in other contigs.

I stitched together the mitogenome with `Contig02+2968` (up to the first long repeat of C's at 10205 bp) + `Contig01+76595951` + `Contig02+11489` + `Contig02+2968` (circularized).
